fornia, and in\nthe Pacific Northwest (Idaho, and Eastern Washington and Oregon). Our framework\ndiagnoses where to place air quality sensors so that they can best monitor\nsmoke from wildfires. Our framework may also be applied to urban areas for\nequitable placement of PM2.5 monitors.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Jan 2022 08:44:29 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 16 Feb 2022 21:01:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-18"}
